Ad Text:
About Us

From humble beginnings in 2011, Evolution Mining is now a leading gold producer, operating six mines across Australia and Canada. Enacting our vision to be inspired people creating a premier global gold company, we are indeed a bold team with a bright future. Our operational diversity offers our employees access to many experiences and career opportunities within the one company. So, whether you choose to work at one of our underground or open pit operations, explore for our future as part of our Discovery team, or join our Group Office, we know you'll have a bright future with us.


At Cowal

At Cowal, our substantial investment has led to a longer mine life as we have boldly reimagined our future to 2040. Located near West Wyalong in central New South Wales, Cowal is a residential site where we encourage our people to live nearby and enjoy the close-knit communities and lifestyles of the surrounding areas.



Your Benefits

At Evolution, we support, develop and reward everyone who chooses to be a part of our bright future. Your benefits include relocation assistance, salary packaging (i.e. novated car leasing, remote area housing), life insurance and income protection, quarterly performance bonuses, employee share scheme, referral bonuses, recognition program, study assistance, discounted health insurance, discounted gym membership. Bus transportation is provided to and from West Wyalong at the beginning and end of your shift.


The roster is 5:2 / 4:3, 10 hour day shifts. Flexible working arrangements will be considered, and this opportunity is offered as a 12 month secondment.


We understand that flexible work means something different to everyone and encourage you to have a conversation about the flexible work options available.



About the Role
This is a high impact Business Analyst role within our Commercial team at Cowal, supporting informed, disciplined and effective operational decision making across the site.



Reporting to the Commercial Manager and Commercial Superintendent, you will provide commercial insight, interrogation and analysis that directly influences operating, tactical and strategic decisions. This is a hands on, assignment driven position focused on understanding the business, challenging assumptions and improving outcomes.



In this role, you will:



Deliver financial evaluations, business cases and trade off studies to support capital and operational decisions
Analyse site performance through cost, variance, trend and benchmarking analysis to identify efficiency and improvement opportunities
Support budget, forecast and Life of Mine planning, including short term forecasts
Evaluate business improvement initiatives and validate outcomes through post implementation reviews
Work closely with Operations to provide practical, data driven insights that improve commercial discipline
Build strong relationships with site leadership, corporate finance and cross‑functional stakeholders



This role offers strong visibility, variety and development, with exposure to senior leadership and the opportunity to genuinely influence how the operation is run.

About You
You are a commercially minded analyst who enjoys getting into the detail, asking the right questions and turning data into actionable insight.



We are seeking candidates with the ability to think commercially, analyse operational data and partner effectively with the business.



You will bring:



Strong analytical capability with the ability to interpret complex operational and financial data
Advanced to strong Excel skills and experience working with large data sets
Exposure to ERP systems (Pronto preferred) and tools such as Power BI and Power Query
The confidence to challenge assumptions and present clear, balanced recommendations
Strong communication skills and the ability to engage stakeholders at all levels
Experience in mining, heavy industry or similar operational environments will be highly regarded, as will backgrounds in geology, engineering, cost analysis, business improvement or operational excellence.
Tertiary qualifications in Engineering, Finance, Commerce, Accounting, Data Science or similar (desirable)



Above all, you're curious, commercially astute and motivated to deliver better outcomes - safely, collaboratively and with accountability.


At Evolution, as our name suggests, change and transformation is in our DNA. We want the Evolution experience to be your career highlight. We are an equal opportunity employer committed to creating a more inclusive and diverse workforce that represents the communities in which we operate. We provide a recruitment process that is fair, equitable and accessible for all and candidates from all backgrounds are encouraged to apply. We are focused on keeping our people safe and healthy and creating sustainable value in an environmentally and socially responsible way. Join our bold team to start your next exciting chapter.


To find out more about us and Cowal, click here https://joinus.evolutionmining.com/


We thank you for taking the time to submit your application.

Ad Text:
Senior Business Systems Analyst
Campbelltown, Sydney NSW or Brisbane QLD

Lead Real Transformation in an Asset-Intensive Environment

We are partnering with a national business operating in the utilities and infrastructure services sector, supporting cities, councils and private organisations to manage and maintain critical network assets. The focus is underpinned by excellence in customer service, innovation and safety and they are investing heavily in how the systems, data and workflows support that mission.

We're seeking a Senior Business Systems Analyst to play a pivotal role in the operational and digital transformation journey.

This is not a maintenance role. This is a transformation role.

If you've worked in Telco, Civil, Construction, Energy, Utilities or Manufacturing, you'll understand complex field operations, asset-heavy environments, multiple systems that don't always talk to each other and the value created when they finally do.

The Opportunity

Reporting to the General Manager, you will take ownership of reviewing, integrating and optimising core business systems (primarily Kynection), ensuring they drive measurable performance across Operations, Finance, HR and Reporting.

You'll work closely with frontline field teams, supervisors and senior leaders to redesign workflows, eliminate duplication, improve data integrity and unlock meaningful business insights.

You will:

Systems Strategy & Optimisation

Lead the integration and optimisation of core business systems
Analyse and redesign workflows across operational, financial and people functions
Reduce data duplication and improve accuracy, consistency and ease of use
Develop business intelligence frameworks and build hands on Power BI dashboards
Present clear recommendations, business cases and improvement options

System Design & Performance

Build, test and implement automation and workflow improvements
Monitor system performance and troubleshoot complex integration and data issues
Design system solutions that reflect real operational requirements
Play a key role in the organisation's operational and digital transformation

Change & Stakeholder Leadership

Support change management by driving system adoption and engagement
Oversee the rollout of approved changes to ensure smooth implementation
Engage directly with frontline teams to understand real-world system usage
Ensure measurable business outcomes are achieved

What We're Looking For

You're a systems-focused professional with strong technical capability and the confidence to own complex workflows and reporting requirements.

You will bring:

Experience integrating or improving business systems (Kynection, simPRO, MYOB, Upvise, Pronto or similar)
Strong process mapping capability (AS IS / TO BE design)
Hands-on Power BI experience - data modelling, system connections and dashboard development
Experience delivering automation, reporting improvements or workflow simplification
Strong communication skills with the ability to engage senior leaders and field teams
Excellent problem-solving ability and a high-delivery mindset
Willingness to travel between NSW and QLD for discovery and implementation work

Experience within Telco, Civil, Construction, Energy, Utilities or Manufacturing environments will be highly regarded.

Why This Role?

Be part of a genuine transformation program with visible operational impact
Work in a business where system improvements directly improve field and customer outcomes
Join a values-driven organisation built on teamwork, service, safety and respect
Influence how a growing national business scales its systems and performance

If you're ready to drive meaningful systems transformation in a hands-on, operational environment, please apply and we will be intocuh for a chat.

The Opportunity:

Exceptional communication skills and attention to detail.

As a Lead Data Scientist, you'll lead a growing data science team and play a pivotal role in shaping and delivering data-driven solutions across stakeholders. Your primary responsibilities include leading and mentoring your team, designing and implementing advanced machine learning and statistical models, translating complex business problems into scalable data products, and leading the end-to-end lifecycle from discovery to production. You will lead by example with modern data science techniques and tooling, providing clear technical direction and coaching to team members. 

We’re looking for a collaborative team player who thrives in a dynamic environment, embraces the challenge of legacy systems, remains composed under pressure, and is driven to deliver continuous improvement and strategic impact.  This role provides a unique opportunity to connect directly with our stakeholders.  You should be a versatile data leader who can both drive hands-on delivery and lead the development of new data initiatives—balancing strategic oversight with practical execution. 

 

 

Job Description

On a typical day you will: 

Lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (up to10 people) and set the technical direction and standards 
Collaborate within a cross-functional digital team, including Product Management, Engineering and Design. 
Bridge the gap between business problems and data science solutions, turning opportunities into impactful, production-ready models. 
Utilise strong analytical and modelling skills to design, build, and validate machine learning solutions, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), neural networks, and transformer-based approaches. 
Define and lead the end-to-end lifecycle of data products in an agile environment, from problem framing and experimentation through to deployment and monitoring. 
Conduct and document detailed analysis, including business case development, to prioritise use cases and clearly communicate trade-offs and expected value to stakeholders. 
Work closely with data and platform engineers on ETL pipelines, containerised solutions (e.g. Docker, Kubernetes), and cloud-based environments (e.g. GCP, AWS, Azure), with exposure to modern data platforms such as Snowflake and Databricks. 
Collaborate with cross-functional Agile teams (Engineering, Product, Design, QA) in remote and on-site settings, applying appropriate governance and engagement models to data projects. 
Provide BAU support for existing models and data products, while actively managing demand, prioritisation, and stakeholder expectations to create space for strategic, high-impact data science initiatives. 
Qualifications
Proven end-to-end Data Science experience (6+ years), including recent experience operating at Senior/Lead level 
Proven ability to lead, mentor and motivate a data science team (typically 3–10 people) and to set technical direction and standards 
Strong, hands-on expertise with modern machine learning models and algorithms, particularly tree-based methods (e.g. XGBoost, GBM, LightGBM), statistical models, and neural networks 
Demonstrated experience working with LLMs, transformers and embeddings in practical, production-oriented use cases 
Solid understanding of the end-to-end lifecycle of data products, from problem framing and model development through to productisation, pipelining and BAU support 
Proficiency in Python and a strong command of SQL for data exploration, feature engineering and model implementation 
Experience working with cloud platforms (e.g. GCP, AWS or Azure) and familiarity with modern data ecosystems such as Snowflake and/or Databricks (or ability to upskill quickly) 
Exposure to containerised solutions (e.g. Docker) and collaborating with engineers on production deployment and MLOps practices 
Strong stakeholder management and communication skills, with the ability to translate business problems into data solutions and tell a compelling story with insights 
Experience contributing to or leading governance and engagement models (e.g. steering committees, RACI/RASCI frameworks, working groups) across multiple stakeholders 
Demonstrated capability in prioritisation and managing tradeoffs in a resourceconstrained or scaleup environment, including pushing back on lowvalue work 
Experience developing or contributing to business cases for data and AI initiatives, including articulating value, risks and assumptions 
Additional Information

Lendi Group teams operate across Australia and the Philippines. Bringing together diverse expertise, innovative technology and a customer-first approach, our teams work seamlessly to simplify the property journey, helping Australians find, buy and own property with confidence.

Generous paid Parental Leave: we celebrate our growing Lendi Group family with 18-26 weeks leave for primary carers and up to 4 weeks for secondary carers.
An additional week’s Loyalty Leave each year after reaching 3 years’ service.
Wellness initiatives with a strong focus on psychological safety.

Business Analyst – Enterprise Operations

About IVE

IVE Group is Australia’s leading holistic marketing company. With an unmatched breadth and depth of offering, we guide our clients from idea to execution. Our landscape is constantly evolving — and so are we.

We specialise in creative, data-driven communications, integrated marketing, production and distribution, bringing together the capabilities, specialists and technology needed to make customer connection seamless.

About the role

We’re looking for a commercially minded Business Analyst to support a major evolution in how we service and grow enterprise clients across our Creative, Production (Warehousing & Logistics), and Marketing Operations.

Working closely with senior and executive leadership, you’ll analyse current operating models, assess profitability, and help design optimised, future-fit ways of working across creative, production, supply chain, warehousing, logistics and account management.

This is a hands-on, insight-led role for someone who is curious by nature, comfortable with complexity, and able to translate data into clear, practical insights that inform real business decisions.

How You’ll Work

You’ll work across stakeholders to understand how our business operates end-to-end – reviewing processes, analysing performance, and identifying where change will create the most value.

A key focus of the role is understanding and optimising our warehousing and distribution operations – reviewing how stock is stored, moved and dispatched, and identifying opportunities to improve cost, efficiency and scalability.

You’ll draw on best-in-class operational and fulfilment practices to help evolve how we operate and deliver value to clients.

You won’t be writing technical specifications or delivering systems. Instead, you’ll translate insight into clear, actionable recommendations and work with leadership to help shape outcomes.

Key Responsibilities

Analyse operating models across enterprise accounts

Assess profitability by account, service and activity

Identify operational and commercial improvement opportunities

Build commercial scenarios to evaluate alternative operating models

Synthesise data across Finance, Operations and Account Management

Develop fact-based narratives to support leadership decision-making

Identify meaningful data sources to inform analysis and insight

Partner with Account Management, Finance and Operations on cost drivers, utilisation and performance

What You’ll Bring

Strong analytical capability and confidence working with data (Excel fluency expected)

Ability to map processes, identify inefficiencies and drive improvement

Experience translating analysis into clear, actionable recommendations

Confidence working across stakeholders and influencing decision-making

Curiosity, sound judgement, and comfort operating in ambiguity

Experience in business analysis, commercial analysis or consulting

The Portfolio Performance & Insights Lead plays a critical role across a national self-insured workers’ compensation program spanning all Australian jurisdictions. This role sits at the intersection of business performance, analytics, and technology enablement. 


This role is a hands-on performance leader responsible for personally designing, building, and delivering high-quality portfolio performance reporting and insights across a national, multi-jurisdiction self-insured workers’ compensation program. This role will enable insight-led decision-making, translation of business needs into analytics requirements, and delivery through technology platforms The Lead will work closely with DXC and customer leadership to shape priorities, while directly producing the reports, dashboards, and insights that drive financial performance, operational consistency, and improved injured worker outcomes. 

Location for this role is flexible. Successful candidate can be based in any major city in Australia.


Key Responsibilities 

Reporting & Insight Delivery (Primary Accountability) 

Strategic owner of performance insights 

Design, build, and deliver national portfolio performance reports, dashboards, and insight packs for DXC and customer governance forums. 

Develop consolidated national views while appropriately reflecting jurisdictional differences across Australian workers’ compensation schemes. 

Produce clear, accurate, and timely reporting covering key financial and operational drivers including claims cost, duration, medical and treatment spend, weekly benefits, common law exposure, recoveries, reserves, and return-to-work outcomes. 

Ensure all reporting is decision-ready, insight-led, and aligned to customer and DXC priorities. 

Define and lead the performance analytics and insights agenda aligned to organisational strategy, scheme sustainability, and regulatory obligations. 

Identify priority insight domains across claims performance, injury management outcomes, employer behaviour, financial performance/ sustainability, and risk exposure. 


Financial & Portfolio Analysis 

Undertake detailed analysis of portfolio performance to identify trends, risks, and opportunities across jurisdictions. 

Translate analysis into clear, actionable insights and recommendations that support financial sustainability and improved outcomes. 

Support forecasting, reserve monitoring, and performance tracking against budget and actuarial expectations, with a strong focus on explaining drivers and impacts. 

Performance Leadership & Stakeholder Partnership 

Partner with DXC and customer leadership teams to understand strategic priorities and ensure reporting directly supports decision-making. 

Lead performance conversations by presenting and explaining insights, not just producing data. 

Support customer governance forums, quarterly reviews, and ad-hoc performance deep dives. 

SME Engagement 

Work with subject matter experts across claims, injury management, finance and data teams to inform analysis. 

Clearly define analytical questions and data requirements, while retaining ownership for building and delivering the final outputs. 

Validate and challenge inputs from SMEs to ensure accuracy, relevance, and consistency. 

Continuous Improvement & Reporting Excellence 

Continuously improve reporting quality, automation, and efficiency across the national program. 

Build and maintain robust reporting frameworks, KPIs, and data definitions. 

Identify opportunities to reduce manual effort while increasing insight quality and consistency. 

Act as a technical reference point for portfolio performance reporting within the program. 




Skills, Experience & Capabilities 

Experience 

Strong hands-on experience in workers’ compensation, self-insurance, insurance analytics, or portfolio performance reporting within the Australian market. 

Demonstrated experience building and delivering executive-level reports and dashboards, not just overseeing others. 

Experience working across multiple Australian jurisdictions and schemes in a national program context. 

Accountable for insight adoption and value realisation. 

Technical & Analytical Capability (Critical) 

Primary translator between business needs and analytics capability. 

Business lead for analytics technology enablement. 

Advanced capability in data analysis and report production using tools such as Power BI, Excel (advanced), SQL or similar. 

Strong understanding of workers’ compensation financial and operational performance drivers. 

Ability to interpret, explain, and challenge complex data and actuarial outputs. 

High attention to detail with strong data integrity and quality focus. 

Communication & Influence 

Ability to clearly explain complex performance insights to senior stakeholders. 

Confident presenter who can lead performance discussions using facts and evidence. 

Strong written communication skills with a focus on concise, executive-ready outputs. 

Client-focused, outcome-driven, and execution-oriented. 

Comfortable operating as a hands-on contributor in a complex environment. 

Pragmatic, disciplined, and committed to delivering high-quality outputs.

The Opportunity
This is a time-critical Business Analyst contract supporting a university timetabling platform replacement (Celcat replacement) within a broader digital program. Procurement is complete, the new vendor platform is selected, and delivery risk is now sitting squarely in requirements quality, stakeholder alignment, and UAT readiness. They need a senior BA who can land, diagnose complexity fast, and drive clarity at pace to protect delivery timeframes and adoption.


About the Role

You will own end-to-end business analysis across timetabling and scheduling, from discovery through implementation-ready requirements and into UAT support, working across business, academic, vendor, and ICT delivery teams.

Lead requirements elicitation, analysis, validation, and sign-off (workshops, interviews, artefacts)

Map as-is and to-be timetabling and scheduling processes, including dependencies and impacts

Translate needs into functional and non-functional requirements, user stories, and acceptance criteria

Partner with the vendor and delivery teams on solution alignment, options, and trade-offs

Actively manage scope, assumptions, dependencies, and requirements risk to prevent rework

Support UAT end to end: test approach, test cases, execution support, defect triage, validation



About You

You are not a generalist BA. You are senior, self-directed, and calm under delivery pressure, with the credibility to influence academic and operational stakeholders and the discipline to produce requirements that reduce downstream churn.

Proven senior or lead BA experience on complex enterprise programs with tight timelines

Strong requirements craft: process modelling, use cases, stories, and traceable acceptance criteria

Confident stakeholder management across senior business, academics, ICT, and vendors

Experience in complex environments (higher ed desirable, but regulated enterprise is fine)

Strong testing and UAT capability, including business-focused test design and defect triage

Timetabling, scheduling, or student lifecycle systems experience is highly desirable


The Benefits

Initial 6 month contract with strong scope for extension
Be a critical part of this delivery
Competitive Daily rate

Ad Text:
The role



Manager, Digital Products & Applications leads a team of 10 digital and technology specialists (including business analysts, application support specialists and system engineers) responsible for the day‑to‑day operational management, support and continuous improvement of APRA's systems and digital applications.

This role has a strong operational focus, ensuring digital products and business applications are reliable, secure, well‑supported and continuously enhanced to meet evolving business needs. effective incident and request management, prioritisation of enhancements, and embedding practices that improve service quality, stability and user experience.

As a people leader, you will build and lead a high‑performing team that responds to support requests, resolves issues efficiently, and proactively identifies opportunities to improve systems, automate processes and reduce operational risk. You will also play a key role in driving training, adoption and effective use of technology, supporting the digitisation and optimisation of business processes across the organisation.



The team



APRA's Technology team delivers, maintains, and enhances essential information technology services that support the organisation's productivity, strategic objectives, and business unit priorities.

Technology partner with stakeholders to design, implement and maintain IT solutions that meet the needs of the organisation and ensuring these are secure and aligned with APRA's technology architecture.



Key responsibilities



Lead, coach and develop a multi‑disciplinary team of 10 specialists, fostering a strong service culture focused on operational excellence and continuous improvement.
Own the operational run of digital products and business applications, ensuring systems are stable, secure, supported and fit for purpose.
Oversee incident, problem and request management, ensuring timely resolution, clear communication and minimal disruption to business operations.
Drive continuous improvement of systems and services by identifying enhancement opportunities, prioritising work, and reducing manual effort and technical debt.
Ensure effective training, adoption and use of digital tools, working with stakeholders to uplift digital capability and embed new ways of working.
Partner with business areas to digitise and optimise business processes, leveraging technology to improve efficiency, consistency and user experience.
Manage application lifecycle activities including upgrades, patching, configuration, and vendor support arrangements.
Ensure systems meet organisational security, risk and compliance requirements.
Plan and manage team capacity, work priorities and operational demand to deliver reliable outcomes.
Collaborate with senior stakeholders across APRA to align operational services with business priorities and technology strategy.





To work with us, you must be an Australian citizen with eligibility to gain a defence clearance through the Australian Government Security Vetting Agency.



About you



Proven experience in managing and leading high-performing cross-functional teams.
Demonstrable experience in the delivery of digital initiatives across multiple business domains.
Deep understanding of digital product management practices and human-centred design.
Experience in web platforms, cloud-based services, AI, Microsoft technologies, Oracle Cloud Fusion and integrated enterprise digital products.
Ability to manage priorities, resolve complex issues and drive outcomes in an agile, business-focused, collaborative environment.
Strong stakeholder management skills with the ability to influence senior leaders across all divisions.
Demonstrates strategic thinking, adaptability, and APRA-wide mindset, especially in navigating uncertainty and change.
Ability to communicate effectively at all levels of the organisation.





About APRA

Australian Prudential Regulation Authority (APRA) was established in 1998 as an independent statutory authority that supervises almost 1,200 financial institutions that manage $8.6 trillion in assets for Australians across the banking, insurance and superannuation sectors.

In overseeing the safety, competitiveness and stability of the financial system, we seek to recruit, develop and retain highly skilled professionals, who want to help shape financial services and protect the financial wellbeing of the Australian community. Our employee base of almost 900 come predominantly from the commercial financial services industry or other government agencies; as such, we have the feel of a small corporate organisation that can work flexibly and with agility.

At APRA, we're committed to providing an inclusive workplace where everyone belongs, feels valued and respected. We aspire to attract and foster diversity of background, thought, and experience, recognising that a broad range of perspectives, approaches and ideas makes us stronger, and better enables us to meet our obligation to protect the financial wellbeing of the Australian community. If you need any adjustments during the recruitment process, please inform at application stage so we can do our best to accommodate your requirements.

Collaborate across departments including Property, Retail, and E-com to implement best practices and consistent ways of working.

Advanced SQL coding skills
Experience designing, developing, managing and optimising large and diverse databases and datasets, including maintaining and evolving highly complex data transformations and procedures 
Advanced experience with financial systems and data analysis and visualisation tools, including SAP, Tableau, Excel, Google Sheets, Google Cloud Platform (BigQuery)

About the Role

This role supports the functional analysis and delivery of integrations across a complex ST&A and payroll ecosystem, including Workday HCM, UKG (T&A/WFM), Dayforce aPay, Okta, Saviynt, analytics and legacy platforms.

In addition to hands-on analysis, this position will operate in a lead capacity across the integration stream. You will act as the key liaison between business stakeholders, architects, developers, vendors and testing teams, ensuring alignment across requirements, design and delivery.




You will lead workshops, validate integration approaches, oversee data mapping and reconciliation, and support testing, cutover and go-live readiness. A strong focus is ensuring data integrity and cross-system alignment through integration-led data movement.

You are a senior Integration or HR Systems Business Analyst experienced in complex enterprise environments. You are confident facilitating workshops, guiding solution discussions and influencing stakeholders across business and technical teams.

You bring strong integration analysis capability, a structured approach to documentation and testing, and the ability to coordinate across multiple workstreams while driving outcomes.

Experience leading requirements gathering for system integrations
Strong understanding of HR, payroll, time and attendance and workforce management processes
Hands-on experience with platforms such as Workday, UKG or Dayforce
Experience documenting integration specifications, data mappings and workflows
Strong data analysis and reconciliation capability
Experience supporting integration and end-to-end testing
Strong stakeholder engagement across business, IT and vendors
Nice to Have

This role offers the opportunity to step into a senior, lead-facing position within a significant enterprise transformation program.

Ad Text:
We are seeking a Senior Enterprise Investment Advisor to lead Coliban Water’s investment evaluation and cost estimation practices. You will be the authority on business case quality, investment evaluation frameworks, and cost estimation methodologies, ensuring that all investment proposals deliver value for money and align with strategic priorities. 

This role provides expert advice to the Executive Leadership Team, Enterprise Investment Committee, and Investment Review Committee, shaping investment decisions with evidence-based insights. You will lead a small team of investment analysts and cost estimators, champion rigorous evaluation practices, and build organisational capability in investment assessment and financial appraisal. 

 

Key Responsibilities: 

As our Senior Enterprise Investment Advisor, you’ll be accountable for: 

Lead and continuously improve the Investment Evaluation Framework, cost estimation methods, and business case standards. 

Provide authoritative advice on investment evaluation, strategic justification, and value for money. 

Oversee Investment Logic Mapping (ILM), multi-criteria analysis (MCA), economic appraisal, and whole-of-life costing. 

Ensure business cases are robust, defensible, and aligned with regulatory and organisational priorities. 

Coach and develop your team and stakeholders on best practice investment evaluation and cost estimation. 

Partner strategically with senior leaders to integrate evaluation outcomes into portfolio prioritisation and enterprise planning. 

 

About you: 

Extensive experience (8–10 years) in investment evaluation, cost estimation, and business case development. 

Strong leadership capability, with experience guiding high-performing analytical teams. 

Expert knowledge of ILM, MCA, economic appraisal, cost planning, and whole-of-life costing. 

Exceptional communication, stakeholder engagement, and influencing skills at senior executive levels. 

Experience in regulated industries, utilities, or infrastructure is highly desirable. 

 

Sound like you? We’d love to hear from you.  

 

Learn more in the position description 

 

Salary: 

The salary and conditions for this position will be as per the Coliban Water Enterprise Agreement 2021 Band 6 $142,905 - $152,323 plus super salary range will be offered to the successful candidate commensurate with their skills and experience.  

 

Enquiries: 

For further information please contact Bidita Rezwana on 0431173635 or via email at bidita.rezwana@coliban.com.au 

To apply, please submit your resume and cover letter by 3 March 2026. 

 

Why join us? 

At Coliban Water our people are on a mission to create a better life for our customers and communities – now and tomorrow.  

We love what we do and our location in the centre of a region that takes in 49 towns from Trentham to Echuca.  

Our commitment to inclusion means you’ll feel at home here no matter who you are, who you love, or what you stand for. As part of the team you receive a monthly accrued day off, time off over Christmas, the flexibility to shape your work to suit your lifestyle, and generous parental, carer and workplace study leave policies.  

At Coliban Water we balance a small team rhythm with the reach and resources of one of the largest Victorian regional urban water corporations. 

 

What are you waiting for? We’d love you to join us. 

 

Applicants will need to successfully complete all core training requirements in the expected timeframes and may be required to undertake a Police Check, Working with Children Check, Pre-Employment Medicals or Psychometric testing where applicable. Applicants may also be required to produce evidence of their Right to Work in Australia.  

We welcome applications from individuals of all abilities. We are committed to creating an accessible and inclusive workplace for everyone, including people with disabilities and diverse abilities. Quality & Compliance: Support Project Quality Management Systems (QMS) and ensure compliance with ISO 9001:2015 standards.

About the role 

We have an exciting opportunity for an experienced Financial Planning and Analysis Manager to join our team. Reporting directly to the Chief Financial Officer, this is a highly visible role where you will act as a trusted advisor, bringing clarity, insight, and thoughtful challenge to support strategic decision-making across the business.

In this role, you will manage the FP&A function, providing high-quality financial and economic insights that support business planning, growth initiatives, and key projects across the Company. While the role has no direct reports, you will lead through influence, partnering closely with leaders and the executive team to drive alignment and deliver meaningful outcomes.

You are someone who brings both strong technical capability and a collaborative approach, with the ability to translate complex financial information into clear, practical insights. Your experience in financial planning and analysis, ideally within the resources sector, will enable you to provide accurate and timely guidance that supports confident decision-making.

With a naturally engaging communication style and strong commercial awareness, you build trusted relationships across all levels of the organisation. You are comfortable balancing strategic thinking with hands-on delivery and thrive in an environment where you can make a genuine impact.

 

Roster: Monday to Friday (travel to site required)

Location: Brisbane CBD




Key responsibilities 

Lead the Group planning cycle, including life of mine plans, annual budgets, and forecasts

Develop and maintain robust Life of Mine Plan models, supporting sites with their own models

Consolidate operational submissions and present outcomes to the leadership team and Board

Conduct detailed analysis and scenario modelling on group performance, cash flow, and commodity price sensitivities

Manage the Group planning system (Workday Adaptive), including ongoing development and enhancements

Coordinate risk assessments at each stage of the planning cycle

Oversee capital governance, including approval processes and intra-year forecasts

Deliver financial analysis (variance, trends, benchmarking) to support reporting and cost-saving opportunities

Manage the group cash flow model and provide regular updates to leadership, Board, and financiers

Provide financial modelling and analysis for ad hoc projects, supporting Technical Services and Growth teams

Support major contract tenders through financial evaluation

Monitor external analyst coverage and identify opportunities to align market forecasts with Aurelia’s messaging




Qualifications and experience

Tertiary qualification in business, finance, or a mining-related discipline

Proven experience in corporate planning, financial modelling, and investment analysis within complex environments

Strong understanding of mining processes and value chain interdependencies

Advanced Excel and financial modelling skills

Familiarity with Power BI, QlikView, or Workday Adaptive (desirable)
